cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper deals with identifying polarizing content on social media and predicting future fake news topics. This involves analyzing user behavior on online social media, which falls under the sub-categories of social media analysis (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SD). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) to identify fake news topics. Additionally, the paper deals with cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR) as it aims to mitigate the spread of misinformation. Finally, the paper involves data mining (cs.CY) to analyze the massive Italian Facebook dataset.
